			<div class="postrow has_after_content">
				
				
				<h2 class="title icon icon0">
					Hero
				</h2>
				

						
							
							
							
						
						
				<div class="content ">
					<div id="post_message_1731236">
						<blockquote class="postcontent restore ">
							I've been digging through some old files and have come across a few writing assignments and other bits and pieces that I compiled during my time in college.  <br />
<br />
One such piece was the short fiction story that I wrote for a Creative Writing course.  The professor was one of those super-egotistical guys who wrote something good once and never let anyone forget what an awesome writer he was, but as far as I could tell he wasn't writing shit anymore.  <br />
<br />
Anyway, I figured that instead of writing something fun and imaginative, I needed to write something heavy and pretentious in order to satisfy this git of a teacher.  After all, all the examples he gave us were pieces like Hemingway's &quot;Kilimanjaro,&quot; and other pieces where the author was basically jacking off into the reader's eyes.  So here's my example of that genre, the pretentious short story of super heavy literary heaviness.  Enjoy!
						</blockquote>
					</div>

					
				</div>
			</div>
			
			<div class="after_content">
				
                                       
                                 
				
		        		<blockquote class="signature restore"><div class="signaturecontainer"><a href="http://www.graffe.com/forums/showpost.php?p=1325910&amp;postcount=26" target="_blank">Alikat is more right than anyone who has ever been right in the history of correctness.</a>-Istari  <img src="images/smilies/grinyes.gif" border="0" alt="" title="Grin Yes" class="inlineimg" /></div></blockquote>
				
                                        
			</div>
			
